Auto Loader (commonly in systems like Databricks) has two main file detection modes:
1. Directory Listing Mode
--------------------------
Periodically scans the storage directory
Detects new files by listing contents
Simpler setup (no external services needed)
Slower and less efficient for large-scale directories


2. File Notification Mode
-------------------------
Uses cloud-native notifications (e.g., AWS S3 events, Azure Event Grid)
Detects new files instantly via events
More scalable and efficient
=========================================================================================================================
TRIGGERS

1. Trigger.AvailableNow
-----------------------
Processes all available data in batches and then stops automatically
Works like a bounded streaming job (batch-style)
Good for incremental batch processing

2. Trigger.ProcessingTime
--------------------------
Runs the streaming query continuously at fixed intervals
Example: every 10 seconds, 1 minute, etc.
Keeps checking and processing new data

3. Trigger.Once
---------------
Processes all available data one time only
Then stops
Similar to AvailableNow, but older/less flexible

==========================================================================================================================
MANAGEDFILEVENT->.option("cloudFiles.useManagedFileEvents", "true")
Auto Loader uses managed file events, where Databricks automatically captures file arrival events from storage. Instead of scanning directories, Auto Loader reads these events from a managed event stream to discover new files efficiently.
